metadata.name: The Valley • Landscape study
metadata.description:
Code-generated landscapes inspired by the valley I live in.

This study focuses on building harmonious color palettes, grainy textures and bringing back the feeling of contemplating vast landscapes. Textures are inspired by vintage travel posters from early 20th century.

Main features :
- Random aspect ratio : from 0.67:1 (portrait) to 3:1 (panoramic) with any variation in between
- 11 color palettes : 8 for day time (2 by season), 3 for night time ("Quiet Moon", "Golden Moon", and "Blood Moon")

Press [S] to save as PNG

metadata.name: Teardrop
metadata.description:
I started this work as an introspection to my comprehension on the book of Wumen Guan (無門關), the gateless barrier. 

A question posed by zen master, Wumen Huikai (無門慧開), to whether there was a gate, at a given barrier, where one would wish to pass? There were, of course, infinite many ways to compose such a paradox. 

As I explored through different forms and composition, the gates had become either hearts and/or eyes looking upon us. The barrier (關 guan), a type of blockade of something, effectively became a perspective, (觀 guan), the watching over of some things with love.  

I realized, it was then trivial to debate whether and how such gates exist. And whether something in the sky was flying in and out of gates or non gates, is no more significant than if they were only the teardrops of someone, watching over us, cheering us on. The answer was a simple question of love. 

Press 1 to save png. Chrome only. Preview images are compressed.

metadata.name: Cube City - Upside Down
metadata.description:
A generative cube city. 
Made in p5.js without webGL or any 3D library.
Arrange intensive cubes and strong colors to form interesting pictures.

Main variant is Type. 33% for a Upside Down city. 67% for a Normal.

Other variants:
2 patterns of Background (Stripe / Gradient)
2 patterns of Shadow (Homochromy / Contrast)
2 patterns of Cube Size (Large / Normal)
2 patterns of Stroke (Yes / No)
5 patterns of Fragment & 3 patterns of Stick Length.
And 24 selected Color Palettes.

Total 11,520 combinations.
All variants are selected and based on the balanced state between harmony and conflict.

metadata.name: No Ctrl Z / Volume 2
metadata.description:
The No Ctrl Z / Volume 2 Series was born out of my latest digital art collection titled: "It's never finished and thank god for that". In that series I've decided to go back to basics and generate art instantly without taking steps back or trying to fix and perfect things, layering endlessly till things fall into place magically. Whatever happens happens.
The No Ctrl Z / Volume 2 is exactly the same concept except in this case you create the masterpiece generated out of many mixed layers of paint, textures, brush strokes, scanned artifacts, line art illustrations hand drawn by me and special addon on top such as film frames borders and assorted masking items to give it an extra gritty touch, There are even a few hidden gems here and there, hope you score one.
.
The No Ctrl Z / Volume 2 is even more crazier than the first edition, many more layers, folders and a whole lot of mad abstract variations to please your wonderful self, I am very happy with the wild mixture of this wonderful little experiment.
.
Done in p5.js with the wisdom code of the great @PureSpider.

Enjoy the wildness.
.
Each piece in this series is composed of 6 different semi-transparent layers:
1. 17 Background Flat colors.
2. 11 Textured Brushes.
3. 11 Elements / Artifacts.
4. 19 Illustrations.
5. 5  Sugar on Top.
6. 7  Old Film Frames.

Let the creations begin.
AdidA

metadata.name: Crystalyx
metadata.description: Crystalyxes are crystalline-like artificial organisms with transparent, iridescent and faceted membrane which forms their main body. They are first protocells to have evolved a triangulated mesh capable of rendering simple material properties like translucency, specular shine, color variation and luminescence. Not resembling any organism found on Earth, their compositions are named after precious stones, with the most common one being lapis lazuli. Rare ruby and emerald compositions are also occasionally observed. Crystalyxes come in 3-bit as well as monochrome variants, with latter being rarer. Structure and dynamics of each crystalyx is guided by behavioral features like reconfiguration (affecting topology) and modulation (affecting geometry). They inhabit both darker and light-abundant environments. Some mimic the color of their environment for camouflage, while others create contrasting shades to intimidate competitors. They are rendered in real-time in your browser and can be interacted with by pulling the tips of their facets.
metadata.childrenDescription:
Crystalyxes have seven features which approximately describe their configuration, behavior and appearance. Similar to their predecessors, monocells and chromoplasms, they start from one of four basic primitive shapes and develop in several stages through application of growth rules. Symmetrical crystalyxes can evolve up to stage 4, while irregular ones are known to go even higher. Note that higher stage crystalyxes are GPU intensive to display and interact with. Each crystalyx has both structural as well as behavioral features. Structural ones include starting primitive (tetrahedron, hexahedron, octahedron, dodecahedron), stage (1-6) and order (symmetric, irregular), with many growth-related features remaining hidden. Behavioral features include reconfiguration of node connections and modulation of node distances. Finally, crystalyxes are distinguished by their mineral composition (lapis lazuli, emerald, ruby) and color mode (3-bit, monochrome).

Press o_o for recording an animation clip in GIF format (available only in fullscreen / live mode). Note: this function uses CCapture.js module which can take significant time to generate and download. Press >< for recentering once, double click it to trigger automatic recentering. Coded in JavaScript and GLSL using Three.js and D3 frameworks.

metadata.name: Primeira Busca
metadata.description:
"Aparentemente apenas esqueletos de alguns moradores da terceira camada, existem boatos que eles tentaram atravessar as paredes e levaram choques de alta tensão, alguns deles até está com os ossos queimados, já outros derreteram em espelhos que nunca refletiram seu futuro"
Essa foi a mensagem que eu recebi, mas preciso da sua ajuda para achar um morador novo. Tem mais esqueletos no local aparentemente...
metadata.childrenDescription:
"Mais um morador identificado" 
Graças a você, temos mais um de 60 moradores perdidos , soubemos de um suposto grupo de ciclopes que atravessaram de outra camada, mas só restaram os ossos... será nossa proxima busca.

metadata.description:
Productive design (100% code)

This work is created in the genre of abstract expressionism with a random algorithm that each piece has a unique beauty and charm.
When you look at the pieces of this work of art, you think that it was designed by an artist with real colors, while this art is derived from the unique programming codes that lie in the artistic vision of its creator.

- In this work, 15 color palettes have been used.

metadata.name: Flow 2
metadata.description:
For all those who liked the original—and especially those who wanted an edition and weren’t able to get one before they sold out—here is a follow-up piece.

This series is a collection of animations based on noise fields and fluid dynamics. The pieces are designed to run continuously, and they produce slowly evolving images that seem to drip, swirl, pulse, and flow. Dense networks of patterns emerge and decay as the pieces evolve. Because of their subtle movement, these works make excellent wall art when run on a display monitor.

Flow 2 is somewhat less chaotic and more meditative than the original. It employs different brushstrokes and a different decay algorithm. I also added a number of new color palettes, now 35 in all.

While these animations are most interesting to view at larger sizes, if your performance begins to suffer just reduce the size of your viewing window.

-spacebar will pause the animation

-return will resume the animation

-r will restart the animation

Flow 2, 2022
-hieroglyphica
